item.title: JAGEx item spawning interface
item.dc:creator: @ilyaostr9 io9
item.description:
@ilyaostr9 wrote:

[quote=“semaphore, post:35, topic:55050”][quote author=Asm link=topic=77927.msg883860#msg883860 date=1171106912]
Thus i just found five noobs in this community
[/quote]

I am slightly amused. 
In your count of 'noobs' in the community, I can only assume you were in that group you counted?

Indulge me for a second. I'd like to give you a small pointer, pup. If you find something of real worth, you have no need to go about belittling anyone. The only thing you end up doing is making yourself look like an ass.

This find can be safely chalked up as one of a couple things (you get to decide which tickles your fancy).

First, you all know about the ‘::’ commands. These commands have absolutely no bearing on a ‘player’ account. The only possible thing you can accomplish by using them on the game servers is arouse suspicion… granted not a whole lot of suspicion because they figure if you are dumb enough to ‘try’ actually using those text commands you are more than likely not any real threat to them.

Second, this ‘Enter object name’ does exist in the client. If any of you have noticed the inventory tab screens, you will see that there are 14 tab interface indexes, but only 13 of them are available to us. Furthermore, the index 7 is not known in the client. This interface tab is reserved for people with far more access than most of you will ever see. I would render a guess that this interface gives many fun options available only to moderators. One of those is likely the ‘Find Object’ option. I would render another guess that this ‘Enter object name’ is left in there as a temptation for people with more time on their hands than brains in their head. Although I wouldn’t necessarily guess you would be guaranteed a ban using this, I wouldn’t personally go about forcing this interface to come up and actually try using it.

So to sum up, this is either a mod-only command and has been left in the client simply because the coders CBA to remove it from the main client. Or this is a blatant trap to catch people that are more curious than they should be.[/quote]
Well said, flag-language

Read full topic
